<qti-assessment-item xmlns="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0" xmlns:m="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" identifier="Q28_v13" title="Q28_v13" time-dependent="false" adaptive="false" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.imsglobal.org/xsd/imsqtiasi_v3p0 https://purl.imsglobal.org/spec/qti/v3p0/schema/xsd/imsqti_asiv3p0_v1p0.xsd">
  <qti-response-declaration identifier="RESPONSE" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier">
    <qti-correct-response>
      <qti-value>ChoiceB</qti-value>
    </qti-correct-response>
  </qti-response-declaration>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="FEEDBACK" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SOLUTION" cardinality="single" base-type="identifier"/>
  <qti-outcome-declaration identifier="SCORE" cardinality="single" base-type="float">
    <qti-default-value>
      <qti-value>0</qti-value>
    </qti-default-value>
  </qti-outcome-declaration>
  <qti-item-body>
    <p>Para regular la rapidez con la que se suministra suero a un paciente, se utiliza un dispositivo llamado bomba de infusión.</p>
    <p>En estas bombas, el volumen total <m:math><m:mi>V</m:mi></m:math>, medido en mililitros (ml), que se administra se obtiene multiplicando la rapidez <m:math><m:mi>r</m:mi></m:math>, en mililitros por hora (ml/h), por el tiempo <m:math><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math>, en horas, que permanece encendida la bomba, es decir, <m:math><m:mi>V</m:mi><m:mo>=</m:mo><m:mi>r</m:mi><m:mo>·</m:mo><m:mi>t</m:mi></m:math>.</p>
    <p>Si la bomba de infusión se programó para administrar 300 ml de suero con una rapidez de 900 ml/h, ¿cuánto tiempo, en minutos, debe estar funcionando la bomba para administrar todo el suero?</p>
    <qti-choice-interaction response-identifier="RESPONSE" shuffle="false" max-choices="1">
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceA">15 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceA" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. 15 minutos son 0,25 horas. Entonces el volumen administrado sería 900 × 0,25 = 225 ml, y 225 ml ≠ 300 ml.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceB">20 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceB" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">¡Correcto! 20 minutos son 1/3 de hora. Entonces V = r · t = 900 × 1/3 = 300 ml, que coincide exactamente con el volumen programado.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceC">30 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceC" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. 30 minutos son 0,5 horas. Entonces el volumen administrado sería 900 × 0,5 = 450 ml, y 450 ml ≠ 300 ml.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
      <qti-simple-choice identifier="ChoiceD">60 minutos<qti-feedback-inline identifier="FB_ChoiceD" outcome-identifier="FEEDBACK">Incorrecto. 60 minutos son 1 hora. Entonces el volumen administrado sería 900 × 1 = 900 ml, y 900 ml ≠ 300 ml.</qti-feedback-inline></qti-simple-choice>
    </qti-choice-interaction>
    <qti-feedback-block identifier="show" outcome-identifier="SOLUTION" show-hide="show">
      <qti-content-body>
        <p><strong>Resolución paso a paso</strong></p>
        <ol>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 1: Usar la relación entre volumen, rapidez y tiempo</strong></p>
            <p>El enunciado indica que:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Como se conoce el volumen total y la rapidez, despejamos el tiempo:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                    <m:mi>r</m:mi>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 2: Sustituir los datos del problema</strong></p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>300</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>900</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>t</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>El tiempo es <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> de hora.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 3: Convertir de horas a minutos</strong></p>
            <p>Una hora tiene 60 minutos, entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>60</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>20</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>Por lo tanto, la bomba debe funcionar 20 minutos.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Paso 4: Verificar con la fórmula original</strong></p>
            <p>20 minutos corresponden a <m:math><m:mfrac><m:mn>1</m:mn><m:mn>3</m:mn></m:mfrac></m:math> de hora. Entonces:</p>
            <p>
              <m:math>
                <m:mrow>
                  <m:mi>V</m:mi>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>900</m:mn>
                  <m:mo>·</m:mo>
                  <m:mfrac>
                    <m:mn>1</m:mn>
                    <m:mn>3</m:mn>
                  </m:mfrac>
                  <m:mo>=</m:mo>
                  <m:mn>300</m:mn>
                </m:mrow>
              </m:math>
            </p>
            <p>La verificación coincide con los 300 ml del enunciado.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Conclusión</strong></p>
            <p>La alternativa correcta es <strong>20 minutos</strong>, es decir, la <strong>opción B</strong>.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </qti-content-body>
    </qti-feedback-block>
  </qti-item-body>
  <qti-response-processing>
    <qti-response-condition>
      <qti-response-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SCORE">
          <qti-base-value base-type="float">1</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceB</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceC</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else-if>
        <qti-match>
          <qti-variable identifier="RESPONSE"/>
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-match>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceD</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else-if>
      <qti-response-else>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="FEEDBACK">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">FB_ChoiceA</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
        <qti-set-outcome-value identifier="SOLUTION">
          <qti-base-value base-type="identifier">show</qti-base-value>
        </qti-set-outcome-value>
      </qti-response-else>
    </qti-response-condition>
  </qti-response-processing>
</qti-assessment-item>